{{Quote|He answers to 'Leebo,' when he bothers to answer at all. He thinks he's funny.|[[Dash Rendar/Legends|Dash Rendar]]|<ref name="Shadows of the Empire (novel)">[[Star Wars: Shadows of the Empire (novel)|''Star Wars: Shadows of the Empire'' novel]]</ref>}}
'''LE-BO2D9''', nicknamed '''Leebo''', was a [[Cybot Galactica/Legends|Cybot Galactica]] [[LE-series repair droid]] owned by [[Dash Rendar/Legends|Dash Rendar]] during the [[Galactic Civil War/Legends|Galactic Civil War]].

==Biography==
[[File:DashLeebo-SOTETC.jpg|left|thumb|Leebo and Dash under fire]]
Being a basic issue of [[LE-series repair droid|LE repair droid]], Leebo worked in [[Esseles starport]] as a safety standards inspector. At one time, an unknown transport vessel took off while being checked by the [[Droid/Legends|droid]], making Leebo an unwilling stowaway. From that moment forward, LE-BO2D9 began to work as a ship [[Technician/Legends|mechanic]], going from one owner to another throughout the years. He served multiple masters and each of them updated his abilities and skills, allowing Leebo to do more and more. Finally, he came to the hands of [[Corellian/Legends|Corellian]] [[Pilot/Legends|pilot]] and [[Mercenary/Legends|mercenary]] Dash Rendar. Dash acquired the droid as payment from the [[Rodian/Legends|Rodian]] comedian [[Kood Gareeda]], and Dash seemed to believe his new possession acquired his former master's dry sense of humor.

Leebo accompanied Dash during his trip to [[Hoth/Legends|Hoth]], piloting his [[Light freighter/Legends|light freighter]], [[Outrider/Legends|''Outrider'']], away from [[Echo Base/Legends|Echo Base]] and into the [[Hoth asteroid field/Legends|Hoth asteroid field]] following the [[Galactic Empire/Legends|Imperial]] [[Battle of Hoth/Legends|attack]]. He later aided Dash during his escapades on [[Ord Mantell/Legends|Ord Mantell]], [[Gall/Legends|Gall]], on bodyguard mission to protect [[Luke Skywalker/Legends|Luke Skywalker]] given by [[Leia Organa Solo/Legends|Princess Leia]], the assault on Imperial [[Freighter/Legends|freighter]], ''[[Suprosa]]'', and then the rescue of [[Leia Organa Solo/Legends|Leia Organa]] from [[Xizor's Palace]], always guarding ''Outrider'' while offering Dash advice during his travels.<ref name="Star Wars: Shadows of the Empire (video game)" /> 

After the rescue of Princess Leia, he received Dash back to the ''Outrider''.<ref name="SE6" /> Leebo summoned the [[Rogue Squadron/Legends|Rogue Quadron]] for support for their escape from [[Coruscant/Legends|Imperial Center]],<ref name="Secrets" /> and also piloted the ship at the [[Battle over Coruscant]], while Rendar was manning the [[Turret/Legends|gun turret]]. At the end of the [[Starfighter combat/Legends|dogfight]], Leebo was at the cockpit of the ''Outrider'' when Rendar made a last-second escape into [[Hyperspace/Legends|hyperspace]], avoiding destruction in the maelstrom of debris from the exploded ''Falleen's Fist''.<ref name="Star Wars: Shadows of the Empire (video game)" /> To everyone else, it seemed as if the ''Outrider'' was destroyed and everyone onboard were killed.<ref name="Star Wars: Shadows of the Empire novel">[[Star Wars: Shadows of the Empire (novel)|''Star Wars: Shadows of the Empire'' novel]]</ref><ref name="SE6">[[Shadows of the Empire 6|''Shadows of the Empire'' 6]]</ref>

==Characteristics==
[[File:Leebo.jpg|thumb|Leebo, working on the ''Outrider'']]
{{Quote|We'll never get paid if you stay here all day!|Leebo|audio=Leebo.flac|<ref name="Star Wars: Shadows of the Empire (video game)">[[Star Wars: Shadows of the Empire (video game)|''Star Wars: Shadows of the Empire'' video game]]</ref>}}
Leebo often carried a bag with necessary tools with him. Some of his worn out components were replaced by new ones throughout his operation, giving out a visual mixture of both old and new metal parts.<ref name="Secrets" />

Equipped with specialized [[Sensor/Legends|sensors]], [[Holoprojector/Legends|holoprojector]], single-channel long-range [[Comlink/Legends|comlink]], and [[Computer terminal|computer]] interface, he was a skilled mechanic and pilot. His programming, being updated by every owner, was far more sophisticated than that installed on stock LE repair droids.

Because he'd had few, if any, [[Memory wipe/Legends|memory wipes]] throughout his life, he'd developed a personality and specific sense of humor.

==Behind the scenes==
{{Quote|We just thought Leebo was a neat nickname for a droid.|[[Jon Knoles]]|<ref name="Secrets">''[[The Secrets of Star Wars: Shadows of the Empire]]''</ref>}}
Leebo was named after [[LucasArts]] art department technical artist [[Mike Levine|Mike "Leebo" Levine]].<ref name="Secrets" />

Leebo was voiced by [[Tom Kane]] in [[Star Wars: Shadows of the Empire|Shadows of The Empire]].

